I went here for lunch recently and enjoyed the salad with homegrown vegetables, including watercress & assorted lettuce leaves. It was dressed with the local style Dalat sweet & sour vinegar & was very fresh & delicious. Many customers were eating what seemed like a veritable buffet selection of food at their long table. I asked them where they were from as I overheard them speaking Eglish & they were mostly from Saigon (HCMC). They sad they really enjoyed the quality and wide selection of Vietnamese dishes available at this restaurant. They also had a few kids who were able to run around nearby & have fun without being too close so as to interrupt the conversation at the tables. I noticed live fish in large tanks which had air pumped into them so I guess they had fish on the menu! There is also a bbq set up outside the thatched roof kitchen building, which is separate to the main restaurant building. After I ate I went for a wee walk up solid concrete paths to a western style toilet block! It was then that I noticed 4 or 5 smaller thatched roof huts dotted along the paths & gardens on the hill above the main restaurant. On closer inspection, these were like private dining Burres, all with great views out over the lake. My dog & I had a very enjoyable time eating here and wandering around exploring. Best to go when you have some time as it's a 20 - 25 min drive from the centre of town. There was plenty of shady parking spaces for cars & bikes.

name: C∆°m T·∫•m M∆°i
address: 43 ƒë∆∞·ªùng 3/2 Ph∆∞·ªùng 1, Da Lat 60000 Vietnam
description:
My group of friends and I recently had a wonderful meal at a broken rice restaurant in the city. This was our first time here, and we were really pleased with our experience. Below are the points we found noteworthy and wanted to share on TripAdvisor.

First, the restaurant space is very comfortable and clean. We had a large table to sit together and the space between the tables was large enough to create a sense of privacy. The interior is beautifully decorated with warm colors and creates a welcoming feel. The service staff were very enthusiastic and friendly, they met all our requests and made sure we felt comfortable throughout our stay.

Regarding food, we enjoyed a delicious meal of broken rice. Broken rice is delicately processed, the rice grains are soft and delicious. We have a wide selection of meats such as pork, chicken and eggs. Every dish is freshly prepared and beautifully presented on the plate. In particular, side dishes such as fried eggs, fish sauce and raw vegetables are also great. The quality and taste of the food really surpassed our expectations.

The prices are also very reasonable and consistent with the quality of food and service we received. The combination of quality, taste and price created a memorable dining experience for us. We feel that we received good value for the money we paid.

In summary, we are very satisfied with our experience at this broken rice restaurant. If you're looking for a place to enjoy a delicious and budget-friendly broken rice meal, I definitely recommend coming here. I will come back in the future and explore more of this restaurant's other dishes.

Some friends and I decided to have a dinner at this restaurant on Christmas eve while we were in Dalat. It was quite a last minute decision and the restaurant at first was reluctant to take the reservation and demanded a deposit. We managed to talk them out of it. The restaurant has a very charming atmosphere with colonial setting - 5-star for the ambience. They had a pre-set Christmas menu. However, since some of us don't eat meat, we managed to change the meat items to seafood. The seafood that I had was only okay, nothing great. The service was quite slow, maybe due to the fact it was full house on Christmas eve. The bill took forever to be prepared. The wait staff were all polite. Apart from great ambience, I don't think the restaurant gave value for money.

This is a lovely place to sit, overlooking the lake. We had been in Vietnam for two weeks so it was nice to go native with a Club Sandwich - delicious! The hotel only had 10 guests (43 rooms) staying. It's a nice old colonial hotel but there is no pool.

example_reviews: A Short Review: A Must Visit for: Train Enthusiast, Music Enthusiast, Scorsese Movies Enthusiast (the place looks like any of those New York Cafes from his masterpieces. oh, and Cat Lovers - there's a beautiful & surprisingly friendly (& civil) pet cat always hanging around The cafe is filled with interesting pictures from Trains all over the world. Also, one of the owners happens to be a renowned musician and a pleasant company if you get to meet him. Delicious food at reasonable price, warm & friendly atmosphere and clean & sanitized environment We walked into a warmly lit balcony that we could see from the other side of the street. There were 4 clean and neatly arranged tables with a Coat Hanger. As we walked inside, we were greeted with the subtle Jazz music playing on the speakers, soft enough to have a conversation at a natural voice and loud enough to fill the void between the words. Just Perfect. We were greeted with pleasant smiles from a cute attendant who was wearing a facemask. (It isn't hard to miss their smiles). I had a Hot Chocolate (with 2 spoons of sugar) and she had a glass of delicious red wine (Of which they have a big selection) - just perfect! We have tried an array of main course dishes including all of their vegetarian delicacies. Veg Spring Rolls, Veg Lasagna, Phily Cheese Pizza (my personal Favourite) as well as several vietnamese dishes where they substituted meat with some interesting varieties of Tofu. Like the wine to start the meal, we strongly recommend you to end your meal with their Fresh Cakes (Cake of The Day!) You'd love to meet the charming owners who happen to be at the restaurant often. We strongly recommend you to try & support this restaurant that has been a part of the bustling Tourist culture of the Paradise in Vietnam - Da Lat

example_reviews: Good food. Busy, noisy, need to use chopsticks. Good break from seeing everything else. Soup is good.

We stopped at this mountainside road cafe for lunch on the suggestion of our driver who we had asked to take us to somewhere where locals would choose for a lunch stopover while driving long distances. We were in for a total treat! On the menu was wild boar cooked at our table, the most delicious chicken ever - free roaming mountain chickens with a delicious side of sticky rice grilled in bamboo sticks! All 100% local produce. The restaurant looks out onto the valley below, but we sat in a separate hut from the main dinning hut and were shaded by lots of beautiful greenery and flowers. This is one of those rare finds when you just put your trust in a local to lead you to the best place to eat. Well worth eating here. I have photos to add as well when this restaurant is approved, I am just not being given the option at this stage.

example_reviews: We had an okay breakfast here this morning, soup, fried eggs, a couple of white coffees, It's a few doors down from where we are staying, and we found the management quite pleasant and the food okay.

I have visited this restaurant almost everytime i came to Da Lat. the place dated back long before 1975. Owned and run by a family, and probably is the oldest restaurant in town. the food is great; i especially recommend their vegetarian soup noodle, and other dishes with vegetable. they use generous amount of fresh vegie in these dishes. probably due to their long-standing status in Da Lat, the family members seem to never mind changing their own style for a more friendly service, which one can easily found in all stalls, cafes or shops in DL. The staff seems to well preserve their own cool albeit efficient style of treating customers from the subsidy period, when service was provided based on ration stamps. However, if you dont mind their style, you will be able to appreciate the food.

The food here is decent and cheap. We got two tofu entrees, a meat entree, and 3 sodas for about $9. I actually only ordered one tofu entree and a veggie fried rice, but I guess they misheard me? I got the food to go, so I didn't notice the mistake until I got home. They also gave me the wrong drink. I noticed the drink mistake at the store, so it was corrected there. Overall, the food is good for the price. The service was ok. It wasn't great. I may or may not go back again.

description:
The restaurant is located on the central street of Da Lat city. It is very difficult to park cars, two-wheelers will park in front of the restaurant.

Diners coming here will choose food at the counter and then the wait staff will bring it to the table.  The dishes here are mainly made from natural vegetables and tofu.  In the restaurant, the chef marinated many spices in the food.

Cheap and tasty veggie meal of either a huge plate of rice with mock meat & veg of your choosing (just point to what you want behind the canteen style deli counter) or a noodle soup with assorted veggies and mock meats. 55k dong for these two dishes. Price can't be beat. We preferred the veg restaurant near the golden Buddha but this one was decent and near our hotel. Saw a group enjoying a hot pot too. Some of the mock meats are not the hottest but that's to be expected as they're sitting out in a deli style counter. The rice is hot and fresh. Can't fault it for the price paid.

We went early in the morning and we're greeted by smiling staff. Not much English spoken. We were sat down and two bowls of delicious pho appeared on our table. We weren't given a menu...I don't know if they have one. But the food was delicious some of the best pho we've had in Vietnam. Lots of mushrooms and bamboo shoot and some tofu. It cost us only 60 for two.

example_reviews: I was pleasantly surprise to find a Singaporean Chef in Dalat and a great one ! Mr Wai used to own a Chinese restaurant in Kuala Lumpur.His Hainan Chicken and Char Siu are as good and authentic as the best i have tasted in Singapore;London;Paris;New York.Another big bonus is that one can order many more incredible dishes not in the menu ( a day ahead ) to enjoy. Like fresh Chinese style Steamed Fishes,slow cooked Braised Pork,Clams saute sweet and spicy...Thank you Mr Wai ,i will be back very often.
Delicious chicken rice and roast & grill pork are also highly recommended. The best in town. We will definitely return when we visit Dalat next time.

This busy little dessert shop serves flavorful and surprisingly satisfying avocado ice cream (a famous dessert in Da Lat) in small plastic cups. What the shop lacks in ambiance it makes up in delicious sweets and other dessert. My husband and I visited an hour before closing time but the seats were still crowded with local tourists and families giving us an impression that this shop is indeed quite well-known in the area. On the next night, we managed to pass by the shop again early in the evening to try and sample their other desserts but turned around when we saw an unbelievably long queue outside. The shop had other dessert options like local fruit salad concoctions and fruity ice creams of different flavors. They didn‚Äôt seem to have an English menu but at least ‚Äúkem bo‚Äù (avocado ice cream) was easy enough to say.

Food wasn‚Äôt that good and service wasn‚Äôt excellent. We got papya salad and tom yum was ok but phad thais were awful and tasted like ketchup.

Khap Bun Kha - Thai restaurant. - Located on the front of Nguyen Van Cu street, Khap Bun Kha restaurant recently "emerged" as a standard of Thai style restaurant quite "hot" for young people in Dalat. - The first minus point and seems to be the largest is parking stage. Our group of 4 motobikes came, the old guard sat on the phone, and I parked in front of him for more than 1 minute but he still carelessly pressed the phone. When he looked up to see us ... he ignored, continued to press the phone. At this time, I took the initiative to speak out: where do we park when we go to eat? He did not bother to look at us, his eyes still on the phone. Waiting for 5-10 seconds (like waiting for the message to finish), he lifted his head in the direction of the parking lot with an annoyed expression (his face still looking on the phone) .... Then our group parked motobikes in, after finishing it, he looked up and scowled, it was not parked, moved some motobikes over here üò∂. So we had to move the motobikes by ourselves while he was sitting and talking on the phone. I don't know if he is a guard or make statues. So bossy. Restaurant owners should consider this problem if they do not want to lose the first point in the eyes of the customer (the first point is very important). - The restaurant is relatively small, including a ground floor and 2 floors. Our team chose to go to the second floor. The staff were very enthusiastic and cute (different from the car keeper earlier), always smiling and greeting in Thai, the Thai-style uniform is also very impressive. From time to time always smiling. Even during the time of cutting the "giant squid" in the hotpot was so cute. - The quality of the food is great (although some of our friends can't eat spicy food), the quantity is quite good. Price is ok. Compared to the group of 8 people who order about 7-8 dishes, the average is about 120-170k / person. Very reasonable. However, the time to serve food is a bit long.

example_reviews: On a rainy day, I was in this amazing peaceful and quiet place call La Mappa, enjoying my time with my colleagues and then my working time. This is a good place for you to work or talk with friends. You will love in the decoration, the soft music of the coffee shop as well as its drinks and homemade cakes.

We dropped after visiting Bao Dai summer palace as it was lunch time. Place looked very beautiful from outside and menu quiet ok so we decided to have lunch in here. Very nice atmosphere, decoration, good as a place for relax, but won‚Äôt suggest to have meals. Maybe we were not lucky cause of Tet holidays. 1) veeeery slow even while there was just one more table occupied 2) drinks came the last ones and they forgot order of our daughter. But should mention that taste of drinks was good 3) they didn‚Äôt have pho, said it is only for breakfast 4) food itself not tasty, but portions quiet big 5) the biggest minus was the bill as first they made wrong calculation (stir fried beef with 600k price for 1 while in menu it was just 245) and also they have Tet surcharge - 20% of the bill! The only place with such surcharge for now. Would suggest them to improve food quality and speed cause atmosphere good. Or maybe just leave only drinks

Nice and comfortable environment, with the symbol of Da Lat- flowers. Food and drinks are yummy and with lots of choices as well. The owner is very nice and friendly to all of her guests. name: Lotteria
address: 1 Nguyen Thi Minh Khai, Da Lat Vietnam
description:
Ordered two burgers and fries which were cold and needed to return them to be reheated.

The burgers were quite small and soggy although the picture on the menu gives the impression that the burgers are of a reasonable size. The fries were tough, perhaps cooked he day before and reheated a couple of times.

Not recommended even if you're hanging out for a Western style fast food meal.

example_reviews: Ordered two burgers and fries which were cold and needed to return them to be reheated. The burgers were quite small and soggy although the picture on the menu gives the impression that the burgers are of a reasonable size. The fries were tough, perhaps cooked he day before and reheated a couple of times. Not recommended even if you're hanging out for a Western style fast food meal.

If you're craving KFC and there's none around and you don't feel like street food, Lotteria is the best place for you. Serving fried chicken and Korean inspired burgers, prices are cheap and are quite filling. The chicken pieces are juicy with batter that's perfectly crunchy and seasoned. I loved the cheese sticks and the squid rings were pretty good too. The burgers were quite small but was still tasty.
I wasn't really impressed anyway, but after I had eaten almost the whole burger, I noticed that it was moldy... That ruined everything, of course

name: Midway Tea & Coffee
address: 292A Hai Ba Trung, Phuong 6, Da Lat 66000 Vietnam
description:
My first recommendation for those looking for a place to work in Dalat.

The place is super large - imagine you put 2 normal coworking space together. This coffee shop is a great match for those who work remotely in Dalat: 
- Comfortable chairs and table setting, like in an open office
- Good music, you can focus on your work
- Good wifi connection and have many charging stations 
- Have tea and water self-refill station 
- Have snack and lunch offering in the menu, with good price

Important plus: with their business setting, this place doesn't have families and teenagers coming for chatting/selfie. Very few customers in the place, so you can concentrate on your work.

You can also buy local souvenirs with good price from them as well.

name: Nha Hang Suong Mu
address: 41/2 Tran Phu, Da Lat 670000 Vietnam
description:
As my husband and I were looking for a good bbq place to eat, we got dropped off at this place by our taxi driver. Our originally planned place was about 10 mins away from this place, when we passed by, it was empty and the taxi driver said it is because their food is not great. He then suggested to go to a place near Tuyen Lam lake, but we refused to go because it was further than where we intended to go after food. 
He basically dropped us off at the first place he saw. We were hungry so we just went in anyway, hope it might be one of those restaurants that not a lot of people know but it is delicious or something.
It turned out the food was just okay. It took awhile to get on the table for sure. The staff were nice but acted like they don't hear or understand me, I speak Vietnamese fluently, not try to confuse them with English at all. They brought out 4 beers instead of 2 like I asked. They took over 30 mins for food to come to our table, which doesn't make sense because the restaurant wasn't crowded at all, there were maybe 2 other tables beside us. 
Then it wasn't the type I ordered. They grilled for us, yet I told them I wanted to grill by ourselves. They definitely took the fun out of it for me. We just ate them anyway. We got 200K worth of beef and 150k worth of shrimps, but as you can see in my photos, shrimps seems to be more worthy for the what we paid. 
Most the time I didn't see any staff, they all went to the back. I had to go look for them to ask for a check. 
I wouldn't go back to this place or recommend it to anyone.

example_reviews: This restaurant is pretty dumpy. The food at other tables looked quite good though. I let my wife order here. She ordered the East Asian Hotpot. What I didn't realize was that meant lots and lots of mushrooms. I don't mind a few mushrooms but what we were served was an overdose of mushrooms and to be honest the hotpot (it was actually a soup) was VERY bland. IF you manage to order the right meal I believe that you might get a good meal here but ours was not enough to bring us back. There are some strange animals on the menu if that interests you at all...

Stumbled across this restaurant which was not on the review list. From outside it look quite ordinary and the decor was also such.The place seems to be very popular with the local crowd and we could see it's quiet established. We ordered what look interesting on the other tables and every dish turned out to be very good. Even the ordinary looking fried beancurd was outstanding. Glad we had dinner there.
